  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How does one configure TCS mail on an iPhone?",
  "response": "Configuring TCS (Tata Consultancy Services) mail on an iPhone generally involves setting up your corporate email using the Microsoft Exchange protocol, since most corporate emails use Exchange servers. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you set up your TCS email on an iPhone:\n\n### Step 1: Get Required Information\nBefore you begin, make sure you have the following information:\n1. Your TCS email address.\n2. Your TCS email password.\n3. The Exchange server address (you might need to contact your IT helpdesk for this).\n\n### Step 2: Add Exchange Account\n1. **Open Settings:** On your iPhone, open the \u201cSettings\u201d app.\n2. **Accounts & Passwords:** Scroll down and select \u201cMail\u201d (or \"Passwords & Accounts\" in some iOS versions).\n3. **Add Account:** Select \u201cAdd Account\u201d.\n4. **Exchange:** Choose \u201cExchange\u201d as the type of account to add.\n\n### Step 3: Enter Email Details\n1. **Email:** Enter your TCS email address.\n2. **Description:** You can provide a description like \u201cTCS Mail\u201d for easy recognition.\n3. **Next:** Tap \u201cNext\u201d.\n\n### Step 4: Configuration\n1. **Sign In:** If prompted to sign in, enter your TCS email password, otherwise proceed manually.\n2. **Manual Setup:** If the automatic setup doesn\u2019t work, you might need to manually enter the server settings.\n   - **Email:** Your TCS email address.\n   - **Server:** Enter the Exchange server address (commonly mail.tcs.com, but verify with your IT department).\n   - **Domain:** Often left blank or provided by your IT department.\n   - **Username:** Your TCS email address or the part before the @ symbol.\n   - **Password:** Your TCS email password.\n\n### Step 5: Sync Settings\n1. **Choose Services:** Decide which services you want to sync (Mail, Contacts, Calendars, Reminders).\n2. **Save:** Tap \u201cSave\u201d to complete the setup.\n\n### Step 6: Verify and Troubleshoot\n1. **Verification:** Check your Mail app to see if emails are populating.\n2. **Troubleshooting:** If emails are not syncing, revisit the settings to ensure all information is entered correctly. \n\n### Optional: Advanced Settings\nFor advanced settings or if you face issues, consult your TCS IT Helpdesk or corporate email support. They might have specific instructions or provide additional settings like VPN configurations.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to access your TCS mail on your iPhone seamlessly.",
